    <body>

      <div type="description" n="monument" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>White marble statue base capital and shaft (<measure type="length" dim="height">0.84</measure> × <measure type="length" dim="width">1.10</measure> × <measure type="length" dim="depth">0.84</measure>) with moulding on three sides.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>Inscribed on the moulding of the capital (ll. 1, 2) and within the front panel (ll. 3-12).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
<p><measure type="length" dim="height">0.02</measure>; apex
for abbreviation mark; ligatures: <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign>, l.6; <foreign lang="grc">ΝΚ</foreign>, l.8; <foreign lang="grc">ΤΗΝ</foreign>, l.9; <foreign lang="grc">ΗΝ</foreign>, l. 10.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date notAfter="0301" exact="both" cert="uncertain" notBefore="0284">AD 284-301</date> (prosopography).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head lang="eng">Edition</head>
<ab part="N"><lb n="1"/><space dim="horizontal" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ὁ" part="N">ἡ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς" part="N">πατρὶς</w> <space dim="horizontal" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb n="2"/><space dim="horizontal" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName reg="Ἀγαθὴ Τύχη" key="agty" full="yes" type="divine"><w lemma="ἀγαθός" part="N">Ἀγαθῇ</w> <w lemma="τύχη" part="N">Τύχῃ</w></persName> <space dim="horizontal" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb n="3"/><persName key="OppAsclepiodotus" type="aphrodisian" reg="Τίτος Ὄππιος Ἀσκληπίοδοτος" full="yes"><abbr>Τ<expan rend="none">ίτον</expan></abbr> <abbr>Ὄππ<expan rend="none">ιον</expan></abbr> Αἰλιανὸν<lb n="4"/><space dim="horizontal" extent="1" unit="character"/> Ἀσκληπίοδοτον</persName><lb n="5"/><w lemma="ὁ" part="N">τὸν</w> <rs type="dignity" key="clarissimus"><w lemma="λαμπρός" part="N">λαμπρότατον</w></rs><lb n="6"/><rs key="conspraes" type="official-secul"><w lemma="ὑπατικός" part="N">ὑπατικὸν</w> <w lemma="ἡγεμών" part="N">ἡγεμόνα</w></rs><lb n="7"/><placeName type="admin" key="cariaphrygia" full="yes"><placeName type="admin" key="Caria" full="yes">Καρίας</placeName>  καὶ <placeName type="admin" key="Phrygia" full="yes">Φρυγίας</placeName></placeName><lb n="8"/><rs type="official-secul" key="proconsul"><w lemma="ἀνθύπατος" part="N">ἀνθύπατον</w></rs> <w lemma="καί" part="N">καὶ</w> <rs type="official-secul" key="corrector"><w lemma="ἐπανορθωτής" part="N">ἐπα<lb n="9" type="worddiv"/>νορθωτήν</w></rs> <placeName type="admin" key="Asia" full="yes">Ἀσίας</placeName> <w lemma="κτίστης" part="N">κτί<lb n="10" type="worddiv"/>στην</w> <w lemma="καί" part="N">καὶ</w> <w lemma="σωτήρ" part="N">σωτῆρα</w> <w lemma="καί" part="N">καὶ</w><lb n="11"/><w lemma="ὁ" part="N">τῆς</w> <w lemma="ἑαυτοῦ" part="N">ἑαυτοῦ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς" part="N">πατρίδος</w><lb n="12"/><persName reg="Τιβέριος Κλαύδιος Μαρκιανός" key="marcianus" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><abbr>Τιβ<expan rend="none">έριος</expan></abbr> <abbr>Κλ<expan rend="none">αύδιος</expan></abbr> Μαρκιανὸς</persName> <w lemma="ὁ" part="N">ὁ</w><lb n="13"/><rs type="official-secul" key="archon"><w lemma="πρῶτος" part="N">πρῶτος</w> <w lemma="ἄρχων" part="N">ἄρχων</w></rs>.<lb n="14"/><space dim="vertical" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab part="N">The Homeland, With Good Fortune, <supplied reason="subaudible">set up the
statue of</supplied> T<expan>itus</expan> Opp<expan>ius</expan> Aelianus Asclepiodotus, the most splendid
consular, governor of Caria and Phrygia, proconsul and corrector of
Asia, founder and saviour also of his own homeland; Tib<expan>erius</expan>
Cl<expan>audius</expan> Marcianus the first archon <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up/was in charge</supplied>.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="II.4" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">II.4</xref>.</p>
        <p>For T<expan>itus</expan> Opp<expan>ius</expan> Aelianus Asclepiodotus see fasti, Governors, <xref type="governors" n="OppiusAsclepiodotus" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">Oppius Asclepiodotus</xref>.</p>
        <p>For Marcianus see fasti: Local Officials, <xref type="local-officials" n="Marcianus" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">Marcianus</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="found" part="N" sample="complete" org="uniform">
        <head>Found</head>
        <p><rs type="monument" key="SouthAgora">South Agora</rs>: Agora Gate: <seg cert="uncertain" part="N">re-used in the collecting pool</seg>. <xref type="plan" n="02" evaluate="all" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" from="ROOT">See plan 2</xref>.</p>
      </div>

